notesStmt.note: 6th and 10th quire are imperfect; lacunae after folios 53 and 84.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A fragment of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on Deuteronomy 1:1-7:10.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 23; written lines: 23; The Hebrew biblical text is embodied.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Square and semi-cursive script of 16th to 17th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Yefet Com. om Deuteronomy. Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2478.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [95v].
